cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper presents a deep reinforcement learning-based job scheduler for scheduling independent batch jobs in high-performance computing (HPC) environments. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of deep reinforcement learning. The paper also involves the use of neural network structures, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also deals with the optimization of scheduling, which makes cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category. The paper also involves the use of autonomous HPC management, which makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of optimization techniques to stabilize and accelerate learning, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category.
